post_text: Hey there all you Superheroes! Our friends at LLS have given us a mission for National Superhero day on April 28th. They want you to show off all your SUPER POWERS and share on social media with #PenniesForPatients. Your Superhero Starter kit with everything you need to get started is posted on Dojo. Follow the activities in the kit and share your Superhero and abilities with LLS by creating a video, drawing an epic picture, or writing a story and you could win some cool prizes on National Superhero Day! Submissions can be made on Facebook by tagging @The Leukemia & Lymphoma Society- Northern Ohio or emailed to Macey.Staninger@lls.org. If you want to fundraise to help beat cancer here is our school's fundraising page: https://events.lls.org/pages/noh/South-Side-Academy-2020 to share with your friends and families across the country. We know that when heroes work together we can do anything, even take down cancer.

Submissions can be made on Facebook by tagging @The Leukemia & Lymphoma Society- Northern Ohio or emailed to Macey.Staninger@lls.org. Four #BGCY50 young men were treated to a tour of the most technologically advanced 3-D printer in the world earlier this week. Michael Garvey, Slade Gardener and Chuck George, owners of Center Street Technologies, introduced the boys to the world of possibilities that come from a career in engineering and design. They were impressed by the enormous size of the 3-D printer, the complexities of the electrical panels and thrilled to meet Alex the engineer. Thank you all for spending so much time and sharing so much valuable information with our young men. #BGCY #bgca #mentoring #engineering #stateoftheart #greatfutures #greatfuturesstarthere #positiveplaceforkids #youngstown #mahoningvalley #youthdevelopment #mentorship #career #industry #business #endlesspossibilities

shared_text:
WALKWITHADOC.ORG
Alternate Route - Walk with a Doc

Oakhill Neighborhood Association
August 6, 2019 at 11:59 AM ·

Look what's coming to our neighborhood!!
Our first Walk with A Doc is scheduled for Monday, August 26th at 6:30 pm. We will meet at Needle's Eye for a quick intro and then head over to our Walking Path @ Irma Davis Park. We are so excited to be bringing this worldwide program to our community!

Our lead Dr. is Dr. Kellie Kirksey, a Holistic Psychotherapist with the Cleveland Clinic Center for Integrative and Lifestyle Medicine. Come and meet her on August 26th and Walk with a Doc!

post_text: We love seeing our students in other settings!
shared_text:
Boys & Girls Clubs of Youngstown
July 11, 2019 at 3:37 PM ·

The smiles tell the story...#BGCY girls and boys were treated to three movie choices, popcorn and soda at Golden Star Theaters Shenango Valley Cinemas. After a long bus ride (and a couple naps), we returned to the #Club where every member received their very own, complimentary individual pizza, chips and cookies from Rise Pies. Everyone had an awesome day and we're all so grateful to our generous donors and hosts! #BGCY50 #memories #fun #movies #friends #popcorn #pizzaparty #yum #goodtimes #fieldtrip #toystoryfour #meninblack #spidermanfarfromhome #infinityandbeyond #bgcy #positiveplaceforkids
